Statements made as to sentencing. Additional statements made by Jennifer M. 

As to COUNT 4-
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 42 MONTHS, concurrent with 13CF722, with credit for 118 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 18 MONTHS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 24 MONTHS.  

Defendant is NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program. The defendant is NOT eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.

Court costs, fees, and surcharges be paid through collection by the department of Corrections from 25% of funds/earnings.

Conditions of Extended Supervision:
1) No association with any gang members;
2) Comply with all rules as set forth by agent;
3) Maintain full time or part time employment of at least 30 hours per week;
4) Pay all costs, fees, and surcharges. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment;
5) Provide DNA sample and pay DNA surcharge;
6) Maintain absolute sobriety from all illegal drugs and alcohol;
7) AODA assessment and comply with recommended treatment/counseling;
8) Mental health evaluation  and comply with recommended treatment/counseling;
9) Provide prescriptions to agent before filling them and take only prescribed medications;
10) No contact with any person or place where drugs are sold, used, or packaged for sale;

